Q.1 Compliance within Fintech – RBI PSS [15M]
a) RBI PSS (Reserve Bank of India - Payment and Settlement Systems)?  
Answer:
RBI PSS (Reserve Bank of India – Payment and Settlement Systems):
•	Definition: RBI PSS is the framework established by the Reserve Bank of India to regulate all payment and settlement systems in India.
•	Purpose:
1.	Ensure secure, efficient, and reliable payment systems.
2.	Reduce operational and financial risks in payments.
3.	Promote consumer protection and financial stability.
Components of RBI PSS:
1.	RTGS (Real-Time Gross Settlement):
•	Immediate settlement of large-value interbank transactions.
2.	NEFT (National Electronic Funds Transfer):
•	Batch-based settlement for retail payments.
3.	UPI (Unified Payments Interface):
•	Mobile-based instant payments system.
4.	Clearing Systems:
•	Netting and reconciliation between banks for smooth settlement.
Key Compliance Guidelines:
•	Banks must adhere to RBI operational standards.
•	Ensure transaction security, audit trails, and timely settlements.
•	Implement fraud detection and monitoring mechanisms.
Conclusion:
•	RBI PSS compliance is mandatory for fintech companies in India, ensuring legal, safe, and efficient digital payment systems.
